Email Copy Advertisement FBI releases trove of 9/11 Pentagon photos March 30, 2017 The FBI on Thursday released a stunning archive of photographs of the devastation at the Pentagon following the 9/11 terrorist attacks.
The photos show the gaping hole in the facade where a jet hijacked by Islamic jihadis slammed into the building, killing 125 along with those aboard the plane.
Other images show firefighters and other first responders battling fires at the complex, debris from the jetlinerâ€™s fuselage and haunting images from the scorched interior of the building.
